# Personal Pod environment template. After the DO pivot (Handover 8)
# and the zkEmail rollback (Handover 9), Pod data lives in a Cloudflare
# Durable Object addressed by the device key. The Worker hosts
# /api/pod/* and forwards every signed request to the user's
# PersonalPodDO. There is no Community Solid Server, no OIDC redirect,
# no provision bridge, and no zkEmail verification in this build.
#
# Values below are baked into the Vite bundle at build time
# (`npm run build`). The dev launcher
# (`bash ~/Desktop/deploy/forum-pod-launch.sh`) overrides them to
# localhost at runtime so you can keep these set to production values.

# --- Production (real domains) ---
# Pod RPC base. VITE_SERVER_URL is canonical; VITE_POD_PROVIDER_URL
# kept as a synonym so existing member profiles keep resolving.
VITE_SERVER_URL=https://secure-worker.forum-community.workers.dev
VITE_POD_PROVIDER_URL=https://secure-worker.forum-community.workers.dev

VITE_FORUM_FEEDBACK_API=/api/forum/feedback

# Pilot WebAuthn fallback (v1.8+). Only when set to 1/true — Capacitor
# no longer auto-enables pilot mode. Use for local APK testing only.
# VITE_ALLOW_PILOT_FALLBACK=1
#
# Worker must have UNLOCK_TOKEN_KEY set (wrangler secret) for production
# writes; set ALLOW_PILOT_BUNDLES=1 in wrangler.toml only while testing
# pilot fallback on device.

# --- Dev (localhost) values used by the launch script ---
# VITE_SERVER_URL=http://localhost:8787
# VITE_POD_PROVIDER_URL=http://localhost:8787
# VITE_ALLOW_PILOT_FALLBACK=1
